{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isQueryDataChar\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isQueryDataChar</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a byte is a valid character in a URI query component,\nexcluding the typical key/value separators `&` and `=`.\n\nInspired by `query = *( pchar / \"/\" / \"?\" )` from RFC 3986,\nbut disallows `&` and `=` so they can be treated as structural separators.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isQueryDataChar","kind":"def","line":302,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isQueryDataChar","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L302-L311"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isUserInfoChar\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isUserInfoChar</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a byte is a valid character in a URI userinfo component according to RFC 3986.\n`userinfo = *( unreserved/ sub-delims / \":\" )`\n\nNote: It avoids the pct-encoded of the original grammar because it is used with `Encoding.lean`\nthat provides it.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isUserInfoChar","kind":"def","line":291,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isUserInfoChar","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L291-L300"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isFragmentChar\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isFragmentChar</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a byte is a valid character in a URI fragment component according to RFC 3986.\n`fragment = *( pchar / \"/\" / \"?\" )`\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isFragmentChar","kind":"def","line":283,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isFragmentChar","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L283-L289"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isQueryChar\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isQueryChar</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a byte is a valid character in a URI query component according to RFC 3986.\n`query = *( pchar / \"/\" / \"?\" )`\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isQueryChar","kind":"def","line":275,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isQueryChar","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L275-L281"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isPChar\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isPChar</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a byte is a valid path character (`pchar`) according to RFC 3986.\n`pchar = unreserved / pct-encoded / sub-delims / \":\" / \"@\"`\n\nNote: The percent-encoding (`pct-encoded`) is handled separately by `isEncodedChar`,\nso this predicate only covers the non-percent characters.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isPChar","kind":"def","line":264,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isPChar","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L264-L273"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isSubDelims\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isSubDelims</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a byte is a sub-delimiter character according to RFC 3986.\nSub-delimiters are: `!`, `$`, `&`, `'`, `(`, `)`, `*`, `+`, `,`, `;`, `=`.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isSubDelims","kind":"def","line":254,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isSubDelims","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L254-L262"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isUnreserved\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isUnreserved</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a byte is an unreserved character according to RFC 3986. Unreserved characters are:\nalphanumeric, hyphen, period, underscore, and tilde.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isUnreserved","kind":"def","line":245,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isUnreserved","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L245-L252"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isValidDomainNameChar\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isValidDomainNameChar</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Char\">Char</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a character is valid for use in a domain name.\nValid characters are ASCII alphanumeric, hyphens, and dots.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isValidDomainNameChar","kind":"def","line":237,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isValidDomainNameChar","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L237-L243"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isValidSchemeChar\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isValidSchemeChar</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Char\">Char</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a character is valid after the first character of a URI scheme.\nValid characters are ASCII alphanumeric, `+`, `-`, and `.`.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isValidSchemeChar","kind":"def","line":229,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isValidSchemeChar","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L229-L235"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isAsciiAlphaNumChar\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isAsciiAlphaNumChar</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Char\">Char</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks whether `c` is an ASCII alphanumeric character.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isAsciiAlphaNumChar","kind":"def","line":222,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isAsciiAlphaNumChar","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L222-L227"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isAlphaNum\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isAlphaNum</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a byte is an alphanumeric digit (0-9, a-z, or A-Z).\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isAlphaNum","kind":"def","line":213,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isAlphaNum","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L213-L220"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isHexDigitByte\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isHexDigitByte</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks if a byte is a hexadecimal digit (0-9, a-f, or A-F).\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isHexDigitByte","kind":"def","line":204,"name":"Std.Http.Internal.Char.isHexDigitByte","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Http/Internal/Char.lean#L204-L211"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Internal/Char.html#Std.Http.Internal.Char.isHexDigit\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Char</span>.<span class=\"name\">isHexDigit</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Char\">Char</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","in